rved between February 2011 and February 2013. It\nturns out that it is often possible to determine low-energy cutoffs early (in\nthe first two minutes) during large flares. Cutoff energies are typically low,\nless than 10 keV, with most values of the lower limits in the 5--7 keV range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 May 2018 01:54:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 May 2019 19:31:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-08"}
